  "prompt_text": "Write a function to serialize and deserialize a binary tree. Explain your encoding scheme.",
  "response_text": "**Serialization and Deserialization of a Binary Tree**\n=====================================================\n\nWe will implement a function to serialize and deserialize a binary tree using a level-order traversal approach. The serialization process will involve encoding the tree into a string, and the deserialization process will involve decoding the string back into the original binary tree.\n\n**Encoding Scheme:**\n-------------------\n\nWe will use a level-order traversal to serialize the binary tree. The nodes will be encoded in the following format:\n\n*   `X` represents a null node.\n*   `NodelVal#LeftChild#RightChild` represents a node with value `NodeVal` and left and right children.\n\n**Serialization Function:**\n-------------------------\n\n```python\nclass TreeNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.left = left\n        self.right = right\n\ndef serialize(root):\n    \"\"\"\n    Serialize the binary tree into a string.\n    \n    Args:\n    root (TreeNode): The root of the binary tree.\n    \n    Returns:\n    str: The serialized string representation of the binary tree.\n    \"\"\"\n    def dfs(node):\n        if not node:\n            return \"X,\"\n        return str(node.val) + \",\" + dfs(node.left) + dfs(node.right)\n    \n    return dfs(root)\n```\n\n**Deserialization Function:**\n---------------------------\n\n```python\ndef deserialize(data):\n    \"\"\"\n    Deserialize the binary tree from a string.\n    \n    Args:\n    data (str): The serialized string representation of the binary tree.\n    \n    Returns:\n    TreeNode: The root of the deserialized binary tree.\n    \"\"\"\n    nodes = data.split(\",\")\n    i = 0\n    def dfs():\n        nonlocal i\n        val = nodes[i]\n        i += 1\n        if val == \"X\":\n            return None\n        node = TreeNode(int(val))\n        node.left = dfs()\n        node.right = dfs()\n        return node\n    \n    return dfs()\n```\n\n**Example Use Cases:**\n---------------------\n\n```python\n# Create a binary tree\nroot = TreeNode(1)\nroot.left = TreeNode(2)\nroot.right = TreeNode(3)\nroot.right.left = TreeNode(4)\nroot.right.right = TreeNode(5)\n\n# Serialize the binary tree\nserialized_tree = serialize(root)\nprint(serialized_tree)  # Output: 1,2,X,X,3,4,X,X,5,X,X\n\n# Deserialize the binary tree\ndeserialized_root = deserialize(serialized_tree)\nprint(deserialized_root.val)  # Output: 1\nprint(deserialized_root.left.val)  # Output: 2\nprint(deserialized_root.right.val)  # Output: 3\nprint(deserialized_root.right.left.val)  # Output: 4\nprint(deserialized_root.right.right.val)  # Output: 5\n```\n\n**Ratings:**\n------------\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision):",
